						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Bhramarēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Gajapati: Vīra Pratāparudradēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śukla, Māgha, śu. 15, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of a village Ārumūruguḷḷa, situated in Pūṅgināḍu-sthala which is attached to Udayagiri-rājya for restoration of Bhramarāmēśvara linga (temple) by the king. Further it records that he granted lands in Kandukūri-sīma for conducting various services in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
